<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hausa_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Other systems">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Other_systems">Other systems</span></h3>
<p>At least three other writing systems for Hausa have been proposed or "discovered." None of these are in active use beyond perhaps some individuals.</p>
<ul>
<li>A Hausa alphabet supposedly of ancient origin and in use in north of Maradi, Niger.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>A script that apparently originated with the writing/publishing group Raina Kama in the 1980s.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>A script called "Tafi" proposed in the 1970s(?)<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6"><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hausa_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0">^</a></b> <i>Ethnologue</i> (2009) cites 18,5 million L1 and 15 million L2 speakers in Nigeria as of 1991; 5,5 million L1 speakers and half that many L2 speakers in Niger as of 2006, 0,8 million in Benin as of 2006, and just over 0,1 million in other countries.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.njas.helsinki.fi/pdf-files/vol5num2/bodomo.pdf" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Njas.helsinki.fi</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ethnorema.it/pdf/numero%204/03%20Articolo%201%20Guerini.pdf" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Ethnorema.it</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b> <span class="citation book">Schuh, Russell G.; Lawan D. Yalwa. "Hausa". <i>Handbook of the International Phonetic Association</i>. <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>. pp.&#160;90–95. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-521-63751-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-521-63751-1">0-521-63751-1</a>.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Hausa&amp;rft.atitle=Handbook+of+the+International+Phonetic+Association&amp;rft.aulast=Schuh&amp;rft.aufirst=Russell+G.&amp;rft.au=Schuh%2C%26%2332%3BRussell+G.&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B90%E2%80%9395&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BCambridge+University+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-63751-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Hausa_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.bisharat.net/Demos/Hausa_alphabet.htm" class="external text" rel="nofollow">"Hausa alphabet"</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.bisharat.net/Demos/Hausa_alpha_2.htm" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Hausa alphabet from a 1993 publication</a></li>
